						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab set up in the temple of Svāmilinga.</hi></p>						

						<p>Tribhuvanaika-nija-bhuja-Vīramalla (Bijjala)—A.D. 1163.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated during the reign of Tribhuvanaika-nija-bhuja-Vīrāmalla, <hi rend="bold">Chitrabhānu, Māgha, ba. 2, Thursday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti.</hi> The details of the date regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1163, January 24, Thursday.</hi> It was a day of <hi rend="italic">Kumbha-saṁkramaṇa</hi> in <hi rend="italic">Uttarāyaṇa.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records the remittance of taxes on goats and sheep for the worship and offerings to god Svayaṁbhu Sōmanātha at <hi rend="bold">Kaḍalevāḍa.</hi> The grant was made by Sōvarasa and Ayitarasa, the <hi rend="italic">Sādhavergaḍe</hi> of the division of <hi rend="bold">Tardavāḍi-One Thousand.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
